Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Well situated, two storey office building available in Regina’s bustling downtown district. The site offers convenient access to shopping, dining and many of Regina’s major attractions including Saskatchewan's largest retail mall, Cornwall Centre, Victoria Park, and City Square Plaza.

Well situated, two storey office building available in Regina’s bustling downtown district. The site offers convenient access to shopping, dining and many of Regina’s major attractions including Saskatchewan's largest retail mall, Cornwall Centre, Victoria Park, and City Square Plaza.

The property is currently home to YWCA Regina. The offering will include the benefit of a short term (2-3 year) sale-lease back along with a unique opportunity for redevelopment. The 28,103 SF site boasts 51,108 SF of space over six storeys and is prominently situated in the Downtown district of Regina across from City Hall.

CBRE Limited (“CBRE”) is pleased to offer the opportunity to acquire The Dream Office REIT Saskatoon Portfolio (the "Portfolio"), featuring three (3) prominently located properties in Saskatoon's downtown core. The Portfolio offers significant scale and provides investors an exceptional opportunity to gain immediate market share in the downtown core of Saskatchewan's largest and most economically diverse city. The three properties available for purchase are Saskatoon Square (410 22nd Street East), The First Avenue Parkade (244-250 2 Ave S), and Princeton Tower (123 2nd Avenue South). CBRE is presenting the opportunity to acquire the three properties as a complete portfolio offering, but offers on a sub-portfolio or individual basis may also be considered by the Vendor.Saskatoon Square - a seventeen story, Class A office building centrally located in the downtown core at the intersection of 22nd Street East and 4th Avenue North. The tower offers 229,045 SF of leasable office space and accommodates mixed use retail space on the main floor.

The three properties available for purchase are Saskatoon Square (410 22nd Street East), The First Avenue Parkade (244-250 2 Ave S), and Princeton Tower (123 2nd Avenue South). CBRE is presenting the opportunity to acquire the three properties as a complete portfolio offering, but offers on a sub-portfolio or individual basis may also be considered by the Vendor.Saskatoon Square - a seventeen story, Class A office building centrally located in the downtown core at the intersection of 22nd Street East and 4th Avenue North. The tower offers 229,045 SF of leasable office space and accommodates mixed use retail space on the main floor.

Princeton Tower - an eleven story Class A office and retail tower located between 1st Avenue South and 2nd Avenue South in the core of Saskatoon's downtown. The tower offers 128,693 SF of quality builtout office space over 10 storeys, as well as 15,179 SF of leasable retail space connecting 1st Avenue with 2nd Avenue through an attractive indoor retail corridor.

1st Avenue Parkade - The four and a half storey parkade on First Avenue is Saskatoon’s only standalone parkade in the downtown core. The building includes 9,567 SF of retail space and 479 parking spots adjacent to Saskatoon's most popular shopping destination, Midtown Plaza. The surface lot surrounding the Parkade is currently used for additional paid parking but the opportunity presents significant future development potential.
